# 🚀 GitHub Actions CI/CD: SDK-Driven Render Pipeline

This production-ready workflow uses the **Python SDK** to validate payloads, dispatch async renders, poll for completion, and verify/download artifacts. It includes exponential backoff, timeout safeguards, and seamless GitHub Actions integration.

---

## 📁 Repository Structure
```
.github/workflows/aethel-render.yml
config/pipeline.json              # Schema-compliant job definition
ci/aethel_runner.py               # SDK orchestration script
```

---

## ⚙️ 1. GitHub Actions Workflow (`.github/workflows/aethel-render.yml`)

```yaml
name: 🎬 AethelFrame SDK Render Pipeline
on:
  workflow_dispatch:
    inputs:
      quality:
        description: Render Quality Preset
        type: choice
        options: [fast_preview, balanced, cinematic_high]
        default: balanced
      subject_name:
        description: Biographical Subject Identifier
        type: string
        default: 'Mythical_Dragon'
  push:
    branches: [main, release/*]
    paths: ['config/pipeline.json', 'ci/aethel_runner.py']

env:
  AETHEL_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.AETHEL_API_KEY }}
  AETHEL_BASE_URL: ${{ vars.AETHEL_BASE_URL || 'https://api.aethelframe.ai' }}
  PYTHON_VERSION: '3.11'
  POLL_TIMEOUT_MIN: 240
  RETRY_BACKOFF_BASE: 10
  RETRY_BACKOFF_MAX: 120

jobs:
  render:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    timeout-minutes: 300
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: 🐍 Setup Python & Install SDK
        uses: actions/setup-python@v5
        with: { python-version: ${{ env.PYTHON_VERSION }} }
      - run: |
          pip install --quiet aethel-sdk pydantic httpx
          # Assuming SDK is published as 'aethel-sdk'. Replace with local path if needed:
          # pip install ../aethel-sdk

      - name: 🔍 Validate & Dispatch
        id: dispatch
        run: python ci/aethel_runner.py dispatch
        env:
          CI_QUALITY: ${{ github.event.inputs.quality || 'balanced' }}
          CI_SUBJECT: ${{ github.event.inputs.subject_name || 'default' }}

      - name: ⏳ Monitor Async Job
        if: ${{ steps.dispatch.outputs.job_id && steps.dispatch.outputs.status == 'dispatched' }}
        run: python ci/aethel_runner.py poll
        env:
          JOB_ID: ${{ steps.dispatch.outputs.job_id }}
          POLL_TIMEOUT_MIN: ${{ env.POLL_TIMEOUT_MIN }}
          RETRY_BACKOFF_BASE: ${{ env.RETRY_BACKOFF_BASE }}
          RETRY_BACKOFF_MAX: ${{ env.RETRY_BACKOFF_MAX }}

      - name: 📥 Download & Verify Artifacts
        if: success() && steps.dispatch.outputs.job_id
        id: download
        run: python ci/aethel_runner.py download
        env:
          JOB_ID: ${{ steps.dispatch.outputs.job_id }}

      - name: 📦 Upload to GitHub Artifacts
        if: success()
        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        with:
          name: aethel-render-${{ github.run_id }}
          path: ./aethel_output/
          retention-days: 30
          if-no-files-found: error
```

