## 🛡️ Production Best Practices

| Concern | Implementation in Template |
|---------|----------------------------|
| **Long Renders (>4h)** | Polling respects `POLL_TIMEOUT_MIN`. For enterprise, switch to webhook-driven `repository_dispatch` (see below). |
| **Schema Drift** | `Command.model_validate()` catches mismatches before consuming GPU credits. Fails fast with Pydantic error dumps. |
| **Rate Limits / 5xx** | Polling loop uses exponential backoff (`10s → 15s → 22.5s → ... → 120s`). API errors are logged but don't immediately fail unless `status == "failed"`. |
| **Artifact Security** | Downloads to runner ephemeral disk. Uploaded to GitHub's encrypted artifact vault. URLs expire server-side after 30d. |
| **Idempotency** | `job_id` persists in `GITHUB_OUTPUT`. Rerunning the workflow with same `config/pipeline.json` creates a new job; SDK handles deduplication if `project_id` is fixed. |

